<FREEFORM>
<BLOCK1><TI><UNDER>ORDER SETTING TERMS FOR DISCHARGE</UNDER></TI>
<P>CANADA PROVINCE OF NOVA SCOTIA</P>
<P><BOLD>UPON</BOLD> the application of Joseph Edward Hendsbee who made an Assignment on the 13th day of May, 2004;</P>
<P><BOLD>AND UPON</BOLD> reading the report of the Trustee as to the Bankrupt's conduct and affairs;</P>
<P><BOLD>AND UPON</BOLD> hearing evidence of Edward A. MacDonald representing the Trustee, Green Jain Wedlake Inc.;</P>
<P><BOLD>AND WHEREAS</BOLD> proof has been made of the following fact under Section 173 of the Bankruptcy Act, namely:
<P1>The assets of the bankrupt are not of a value equal to fifty cents in the dollar on the amount of his unsecured liabilities,</P1></P>
<P><BOLD>IT IS ORDERED</BOLD> that the debtor shall contribute the sum of $7,200 into the estate, payable at the rate of $300 per month for 24 months.</P>
<P><BOLD>IT IS FURTHER ORDERED</BOLD> that upon the Court being satisfied that the bankrupt files and pays amount due on his post bankruptcy 2004, 2005 &amp; 2006 income tax and HST returns;</P>
<P><BOLD>AN</BOLD> Absolute Order of Discharge shall issue.</P>
<P><BOLD>DATED</BOLD> at Halifax, Nova Scotia, this 14<SUP>th</SUP> day of October, 2005.</P>
<P>&ellip35; Registrar</P></BLOCK1>
</FREEFORM>
</ORDER>
